## Purpose

Prints a BST/GMT timestamp at the end of every Claude turn so you can tell when Claude finished — handy when you're about to check on something time-bound (a deploy, a queued job).

## Two pieces

1. **`env.TZ = "Europe/London"`** — makes Node-side timestamps render as BST (auto-switches to GMT in winter). System host is UTC; without this everything is an hour off in summer.
2. **`hooks.Stop`** — shell command that emits a `systemMessage` JSON payload, displayed inline in the chat view when the turn ends.

## Settings.json fragment

```json
{
  "env": {
    "TZ": "Europe/London"
  },
  "hooks": {
    "Stop": [
      {
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "printf '%s' \"$(TZ=Europe/London date '+%a %d %b %Y, %H:%M:%S %Z')\" | jq -R '{systemMessage: (\"Turn ended: \" + .)}'",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

## Notes

- `showMessageTimestamps` / `showTurnDuration` settings exist in the schema but don't appear to render in the default chat view — Stop hook is the reliable per-turn timestamp.
- TZ is set both in `env` AND inline in the command — the inline `TZ=Europe/London date` belt-and-braces so it works even before a CLI restart picks up `env`.
- Requires `jq` on PATH (standard on Linux/macOS dev machines).
- Takes effect on next Claude Code restart.